Efforts to have the company’s local representative appear before PAC failed as none appeared.
“Idemia should not engage in business in Kenya until it registers its local representatives with the Registrar of Companies as is obligated by the Companies Act and as resolved by Parliament,” said Mr Kaluma.
“This legal provision has been in our laws since the Companies Act, 1948, to secure corporate accountability and is not new in our laws as wrongly suggested by the High Court,” the legislator said. 



